org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl
Class AeBaseQueueManager

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.AeManagerAdapter
      org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.AeBaseQueueManager
All Implemented Interfaces:
IAeManager, IAeQueueManager
Direct Known Subclasses:
AeInMemoryQueueManager, AeRecoveryQueueManager
public abstract class AeBaseQueueManager
extends AeManagerAdapter
implements IAeQueueManager

An in-memory implementation of the queue manager. All of the queues are implemented with java.util.Collection implementations.

Attempts to find a match for the message receiver among the unmatched inbound receives. If the message receiver doesn't have any correlation data then we're only matching on the partnerlink, port type, and operation. Otherwise, we include the correlation information in the check. If there was no match then we return null.

matchInboundReceive

public AeMessageReceiver matchInboundReceive(AeInboundReceive aInboundReceive,
                                             boolean aQueueIfNotFoundFlag,
                                             IAeMessageAcknowledgeCallback aAckCallback)
                                      throws AeCorrelationViolationException,
                                             AeConflictingRequestException,
                                             AeBusinessProcessException
Description copied from interface: IAeQueueManager
Matches an inbound receive with a waiting message receiver. If a match is found... The reply, if not null, is added to the reply queue so we can track that the process actually replies. A process MUST reply to all of its outstanding replies in order to complete successfully. We then return the message receiver that was waiting for the message to arrive. If a match is not found and the queued flag is true and the inbound receive contains correlation data... We will attempt to queue the inbound receive in hopes that an activity will soon execute and consume the data. The inbound receive will remain in the queue for as long as the engine's timeout period. If the receive has a reply waiting then it will also be added to our unmatched reply collection. If a match is not found and the queued flag is true but the inbound receive DOES NOT contain correlation data... We throw a correlation violation. If a match is not found and the queued flag is false... Simply return null. This case only applies when the caller knows that the inbound receive is capable of creating a process instance. If a match isn't found, then we don't want to queue the inbound receive, rather we'll create a new process instance to deal with it.

Specified by:
matchInboundReceive in interface IAeQueueManager
Parameters:
aInboundReceive - A message that is targeting either an existing activity or capable of creating a new process
aQueueIfNotFoundFlag - If true, then the inbound receive will be queued if no match is found
aAckCallback - optional callback interface used in durable receives.
Throws:
AeCorrelationViolationException - if the unmatched receive isn't correlated
AeConflictingRequestException - if matching this receive will result in two queued replies with the same partnerlink, porttype, operation, and pid
AeBusinessProcessException
See Also:
IAeQueueManager.matchInboundReceive(org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.queue.AeInboundReceive, boolean, org.activebpel.wsio.IAeMessageAcknowledgeCallback)

findMatchForInboundReceive

protected AeMessageReceiver findMatchForInboundReceive(AeInboundReceive aInboundReceive,
                                                       IAeMessageAcknowledgeCallback aAckCallback)
                                                throws AeBusinessProcessException
Finds a matching queued message receiver for the given inbound receive. If matching receiver is found, then the message is journaled and consumed. The journal id of the inbound receive is assigned to the returned AeMessageReceiver. The consumption of the message should also acknowledge that the message has been journaled and delivered via optional durable invoke callback interface.
Note that the caller is responsible for any necessary synchronization. This method assumes that its work will always be done atomically (at least within the same VM).

Parameters:
aInboundReceive - An inbound receive.
aAckCallback - durable invoke message acknowledge callback.
Returns:
A matching queued receive, or null if not found.
Throws:
AeBusinessProcessException

removeAlarm

                           int aLocationPathId,
                           int aAlarmId)
                    throws AeBusinessProcessException
Description copied from interface: IAeQueueManager
Removes an alarm. The removal of an alarm requires it to be unscheduled (cancelled) in addition to whatever other bookkeeping must be done by the alarm manager implementation. Note that removeAlarm will be called by the engine when an alarm should be cancelled (not fired) as well as when the alarm was fired and must now be removed from whatever internal storage the alarm manager implementation is using.
